Movie: Pier Paolo Pasolini - Agnès Varda - New York - 1967
Mishima: A Life in Four Chapters
Review: had to break up my viewing of this into its respective four chapters across two days because something about paul schrader and first reformed and mishima probes the deepest, darkest recesses of my mind and i actually don't know how people watch this film all the way through in one go? my heart is still pounding after finishing it 10 minutes ago???***given that paul schrader has perfected these "man in a room" stories, i'm now wondering... where are…

Movie: What Do You Know About the Water and the Moon
Review: a strong choice to keep so many elements in the frame out of focus. but it added to the beauty and the mystery for me. the sound design viscerally brought me back to the summers i've spent in china.
honored to be training as a filmmaker in the same hallowed (hospital-like) hallways that bora kim once walked
people are ever-unfolding mysteries ... maybe especially to themselves.

Movie: The Hunger Games: The Ballad of Songbirds & Snakes
Review: i’m sorry, i thought this was good

Movie: When You Left Me on That Boulevard

Review: what words do i use to describe how much this movie means to me ??? it totally flew over my head the first time i watched it in 2018. i think i was too young to understand it, ironically. full of sex but no soul, i thought. it's embarrassing how i once held such an obtuse opinion about this film. zizek says in his criterion closet video (lol) that y tu mamá también is not just a coming-of-age story about…

i still want lily gladstone to receive all of her flowers, especially since she made the absolute most out of so little. but agh, did this work so hard to shine the spotlight on the least interesting parts of this story.

Movie: What We Do in the Shadows

Review: !!! new favorite, i think? so odd and lovely.

romance between immigrants and also a visual essay on moss, inspired by mushroom at the end of the world, robin wall kimmerer, and ursula k. le guin carrier bag theory of fiction - reminding dennis lim of kelly reichardt. bas devos somehow peered into my mind and made a movie just for me ???
perfect movie to watch as i start an MFA program and get increasingly stressed about paying my rent HAHA. thank u for making art, kelly 🥺💗
